>>>>> " " == Tonglu Yi <tlyi@126.com> writes:
     > Hi: My system is redhat 6.0 on a PC. NFS can't work. when i run
     > `df' , it can not terminate.  and display this error:
     >         nfs: task 24 can't get a request slot
This means that the RPC socket is congested. Could you use 'tcpdump'
to check whether there are any NFS packets being sent when this
happens?
     > then i try to kill `df` with -9, and it display the following
     > msg:
     >         nfs_statfs: statfs error = 512
This is correct behaviour.
     > what's more, when the system shuts down, linux can't umount all
     > file system. It just says that the nfs device busy and
     > sometimes the system hangs up.  Thanks for any help or advice.
2.2.14pre6-7 both have changes to the RPC code. It would be
interesting to know whether you get the same problem with stock
2.2.13.
Cheers,
  Trond
